  "intent": "Prepare ELISA control samples by performing serial dilutions of mAb207 and mAb210 antibodies in a 96-well master block, then distribute prepared samples to three 384-well plates. Execute step-wise dilutions of mAb210 stock (4.6\u00b5L + 55.4\u00b5L diluent for 1:13 dilution, then 40\u00b5L + 160\u00b5L for 1:5, then 80\u00b5L + 720\u00b5L for 1:10). Create concentration gradients in master block wells with volumes ranging 5-100\u00b5L antibody in 900-1000\u00b5L diluent. Transfer 180\u00b5L to first two 384-well plates and 80\u00b5L to third plate with systematic well mapping across columns A1-P2.",
